<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00/470: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Tunis</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Springs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-28T23:00:00+01:00">September 28, 1938—11
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 28—9:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Department’s September 27, 4 p.m. Tunisia will give her support to France in
                        the event of a general war in Europe. There is great uneasiness due to the
                        absence of adequate protection against gas. In the event that Italy should
                        oppose France the protection of American born children of Italian parents
                        will be a problem.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Springs</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>